---
import WeekLayout from '../layouts/WeekLayout.astro';
---

<WeekLayout
  week={2}
  title="02"
  subtitle="Exploring the city"
  dates="Week 2"
  primaryColor="#FF6B35"
  accentColor="#FFD700"
  bgColor="#fff5f0"
  prevSlug="week-01"
  prevTitle="Week 01"
  nextSlug="week-03"
  nextTitle="Week 03"
>
  <section class="content-section">
    <span class="section-tag">Discovery</span>
    <h2>The city opens up</h2>
    <p>
      Second week and we're already starting to find the most hidden corners.
      The market, the viewpoints, the streets of the historic quarter.
    </p>
    <p>
      That same week, our internships at a company called CodeAhead began. A local company focused on software development, where we had the chance to apply our knowledge and learn from our tutor — working with 3D models and modern animations without sacrificing free time to explore the city.
    </p>
    <p id="typing-text"></p>
    <p>This second week we improved our knowledge of web design and 3D space manipulation enormously. As you'll see with the interactive models below — very useful skills for building "immersive" web experiences that break away from the traditional approach.</p>

    <div class="draw-svg-wrapper">
      <svg class="draw-svg" viewBox="0 0 1000 110" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <text class="draw-text" x="500" y="85" text-anchor="middle">Learning and having fun</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <p class="interact-hint">☞ Interact with these objects!</p>
    <canvas id="interact-canvas" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <span class="section-tag">Photos</span>
    <h2>The week in images</h2>
    <div class="photo-grid">
      <div class="photo-item"><img src="/photos/test_img.jpeg" alt="Photo 1"></div>
      <div class="photo-item">📸</div>
      <div class="photo-item">📸</div>
      <div class="photo-item">📸</div>
      <div class="photo-item">📸</div>
      <div class="photo-item">📸</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    import '../scripts/three-week-02.ts';
  </script>

  <style>
    .content-section {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }
    .draw-svg-wrapper {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      overflow: visible;
    }
    .draw-svg {
      width: 100%;
      overflow: visible;
    }
    .draw-text {
      font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
      font-size: 80px;
      font-weight: 900;
      fill: none;
      stroke: #FF6B35;
      stroke-width: 1.5;
      stroke-linecap: round;
      stroke-linejoin: round;
      letter-spacing: -2px;
    }
    .interact-hint {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #FF6B35;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    #interact-canvas {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      height: 420px;
      border-radius: 1rem;
      cursor: grab;
    }
    #interact-canvas:active {
      cursor: grabbing;
    }
  </style>
</WeekLayout>
